# Android Kotlin conventions

## Architecture
- Follow existing Fragment + ViewModel + binder pattern; do not introduce Hilt/Clean Architecture layers unless asked
- Use `viewLifecycleOwner.lifecycleScope` for UI-bound coroutines
- Prefer `viewBinding`; clear bindings in `onDestroyView`
- Navigation via Safe Args / `NavigationGraphDirections`

## Kotlin
- Prefer `val`, null-safety, no unnecessary `!!`
- Avoid `GlobalScope` / `runBlocking` on main paths
- Keep UI strings in `res/values*/strings.xml` (en + bs/de/ru as needed)

## UI
- Preserve alpine theme / existing hub layout language
- Don't add clutter cards or redesign hubs unless requested
- Toolbar/status bar behavior should stay consistent with current fragments

## Ads / monetization
- Gate monetized hub opens through `handleMonetizedNavigation` + `AdsPolicyStore`
- AdMob unit IDs stay in app code; frequency comes from remote config
